						<summary>

						<p>This is not dated and refers itself to the reign of <hi rend="bold">Mahāvali-Bāṇarāja Vikra māditya-Jayamēru</hi> and states that during the cattle-raid at <hi rend="bold">Kuṟūñjeāḷa</hi> by Mudhudāra Goṇamēṇṭhi of <hi rend="bold">Minikki,</hi> Periyavan fell fighting. It also records the death of another hero and mentions Keḷāmuddhan. The king had the <hi rend="italic">biruda</hi> <hi rend="bold">Bāṇa-Kandarppan.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
